ng, the code only differs if you are coding in 64 bit assembly, so you can compile a 64 bit code on a 32 bit Operating System, but ofcourse you can't execute the output.<br /><br />I know that you knew that, but just in case you didn't, a human can make mistakes <img src=\"http://forum.nasm.us/Smileys/default/tongue.gif\" alt=\"&#58;P\" title=\"Tongue\" class=\"smiley\" /><br /><br />Slackware's size is large <img src=\"http://forum.nasm.us/Smileys/default/tongue.gif\" alt=\"&#58;P\" title=\"Tongue\" class=\"smiley\" /> But it worth it <img src=\"http://forum.nasm.us/Smileys/default/smiley.gif\" alt=\"&#58;&#41;\" title=\"Smiley\" class=\"smiley\" /><br /><br />Command-Line = x10 times faster than any GUI system, if not more than 10 times...<br /><br />Best,<br />Mahmoud",
